NEWS

Backlog / C23 Port Plan

Scope
- Source code: src/em1.c, src/em2.c.
- Build system: configure.ac, configure, Makefile.am, Makefile.in, src/Makefile.am,
  src/Makefile.in, doc/Makefile.in.

Steps
1. Code audit for C23 incompatibilities in src/.
   - Fix non-standard main signatures.
   - Replace old-style or empty parameter list declarations with full prototypes.
   - Remove or rename macros that collide with standard headers.
   - Ensure functions are declared before use (no implicit int / implicit decls).
   - Verify type usage for size_t, ssize_t, sigjmp_buf, etc.

2. Update source to C23 style and safety.
   - Make function pointer signatures explicit.
   - Normalize prototypes so declarations match definitions.
   - Remove legacy constructs obsoleted in C23.
   - Keep behavior unchanged; limit refactors to compatibility fixes.

3. Update Autotools to request C23.
   - Replace AC_PROG_CC_STDC with AC_PROG_CC.
   - Probe for -std=c23 (fallback to gnu23/c2x) and set CFLAGS.
   - Regenerate configure and Makefile.in files via autoreconf -fi.

4. Verify build and runtime basics.
   - Run ./configure and make with the new flags.
   - Smoke-test ./src/em with a small file.

Deliverables
- Updated src/*.c C23-compatible source.
- Updated Autotools inputs and regenerated outputs.
- Optional: note in README or NEWS about the C23 port.

Feature Branches
- feat/o-editor-visual-backspace: visual feedback for deletes in the o raw editor.
